{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"\"Judge, I want to tell you something.\nI want to tell you something."},{"time":4960,"text":"I been watching you"},{"time":6720,"text":"and you're not two-faced."},{"time":8640,"text":"You treat everybody the same.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":11680,"text":"That was said to me\nby a transgender prostitute"},{"time":15120,"text":"who before I had gotten on the bench"},{"time":17400,"text":"had fired her public defender,"},{"time":19960,"text":"insulted the court officer"},{"time":21960,"text":"and yelled at the person\nsitting next to her,"},{"time":24120,"text":"\"I don't know what you're looking at.\nI look better than the girl you're with.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":27880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":29600,"text":"She said this to me"},{"time":31520,"text":"after I said her male name low enough"},{"time":34080,"text":"so that it could\nbe picked up by the record,"},{"time":37040,"text":"but I said her female name loud enough"},{"time":39120,"text":"so that she could walk down the aisle\ntowards counselor's table with dignity."},{"time":44280,"text":"This is procedural justice,\nalso known as procedural fairness,"},{"time":48000,"text":"at its best."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49600,"text":"You see, I am the daughter\nof an African-American garbageman"},{"time":53320,"text":"who was born in Harlem"},{"time":54600,"text":"and spent his summers\nin the segregated South."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57640,"text":"Soy la hija de una peluquera dominicana."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60440,"text":"I do that to make sure\nyou're still paying attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":64319,"text":"I'm the daughter of a Dominican beautician"},{"time":66600,"text":"who came to this country\nfor a better life for her unborn children."},{"time":70440,"text":"My parents taught me, you treat everyone\nyou meet with dignity and respect,"},{"time":74480,"text":"no matter how they look,\nno matter how they dress,"},{"time":76920,"text":"no matter how they spoke."},{"time":79200,"text":"You see, the principles of fairness"},{"time":81840,"text":"were taught to me at an early age,"},{"time":85600,"text":"and unbeknownst to me,\nit would be the most important lesson"},{"time":88560,"text":"that I carried with me\nto the Newark Municipal Court bench."},{"time":92400,"text":"And because I was dragged\noff the playground"},{"time":95240,"text":"at the early age of 10\nto translate for family members"},{"time":99000,"text":"as they began to migrate\nto the United States,"},{"time":102400,"text":"I understand how daunting it can be\nfor a person, a novice,"},{"time":107560,"text":"to navigate any government system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110920,"text":"Every day across America\nand around the globe,"},{"time":113840,"text":"people encounter our courts,"},{"time":116000,"text":"and it is a place\nthat is foreign, intimidating"},{"time":119880,"text":"and often hostile towards them."},{"time":123240,"text":"They are confused\nabout the nature of their charges,"},{"time":127160,"text":"annoyed about their encounters\nwith the police"},{"time":130400,"text":"and facing consequences that might impact\ntheir relationships, their finances"},{"time":135360,"text":"and even their liberty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137360,"text":"Let me paint a picture for you"},{"time":138840,"text":"of what it's like for the average person\nwho encounters our courts."},{"time":143520,"text":"First, they're annoyed as they're probed\ngoing through court security."},{"time":148400,"text":"They finally get through court security,\nthey walk around the building,"},{"time":151800,"text":"they ask different people\nthe same question"},{"time":154840,"text":"and get different answers."},{"time":157200,"text":"When they finally get\nto where they're supposed to be,"},{"time":159800,"text":"it gets really bad\nwhen they encounter the courts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163280,"text":"What would you think if I told you"},{"time":164960,"text":"that you could improve\npeople's court experience,"},{"time":168120,"text":"increase their compliance with the law"},{"time":171680,"text":"and court orders,"},{"time":173160,"text":"all the while increasing\nthe public's trust"},{"time":176000,"text":"in the justice system"},{"time":177280,"text":"with a simple idea?"},{"time":179520,"text":"Well, that simple idea\nis procedural justice"},{"time":183960,"text":"and it's a concept that says"},{"time":185480,"text":"that if people perceive\nthey are treated fairly"},{"time":188000,"text":"and with dignity and respect,"},{"time":190200,"text":"they'll obey the law."},{"time":192320,"text":"Well, that's what\nYale professor Tom Tyler found"},{"time":195000,"text":"when he began to study\nas far back in the '70s"},{"time":198400,"text":"why people obey the law."},{"time":201080,"text":"He found that if people\nsee the justice system"},{"time":203960,"text":"as a legitimate authority\nto impose rules and regulations,"},{"time":208000,"text":"they would follow them."},{"time":209920,"text":"His research concluded"},{"time":211840,"text":"that people would be satisfied"},{"time":215360,"text":"with the judge's rulings,"},{"time":217320,"text":"even when the judge ruled against them,"},{"time":219360,"text":"if they perceived\nthat they were treated fairly"},{"time":221960,"text":"and with dignity and respect."},{"time":224440,"text":"And that perception of fairness\nbegins with what?"},{"time":227480,"text":"Begins with how judges speak\nto court participants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232960,"text":"Now, being a judge"},{"time":234360,"text":"is sometimes like having\na reserve seat to a tragic reality show"},{"time":240360,"text":"that has no commercial interruptions"},{"time":242520,"text":"and no season finale."},{"time":245480,"text":"It's true."},{"time":246920,"text":"People come before me handcuffed,"},{"time":249600,"text":"drug-sick, depressed, hungry"},{"time":252640,"text":"and mentally ill."},{"time":256120,"text":"When I saw that their need for help"},{"time":259240,"text":"was greater than my fear\nof appearing vulnerable on the bench,"},{"time":263000,"text":"I realized that not only\ndid I need to do something,"},{"time":266080,"text":"but that in fact I could do something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269320,"text":"The good news is is that the principles\nof procedural justice are easy"},{"time":273120,"text":"and can be implemented\nas quickly as tomorrow."},{"time":276200,"text":"The even better news,\nthat it can be done for free."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":279680,"text":"The first principle is voice."},{"time":281680,"text":"Give people an opportunity to speak,"},{"time":283880,"text":"even when you're\nnot going to let them speak."},{"time":286040,"text":"Explain it."},{"time":287320,"text":"\"Sir, I'm not letting you speak right now."},{"time":289920,"text":"You don't have an attorney."},{"time":291280,"text":"I don't want you to say anything\nthat's going to hurt your case.\""},{"time":294360,"text":"For me, assigning essays to defendants"},{"time":296240,"text":"has been a tremendous way\nof giving them voice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300440,"text":"I recently gave an 18-year-old\ncollege student an essay."},{"time":304320,"text":"He lamented his underage drinking charge."},{"time":308120,"text":"As he stood before me reading his essay,"},{"time":310200,"text":"his voice cracking\nand his hands trembling,"},{"time":312720,"text":"he said that he worried that he\nhad become an alcoholic like his mom,"},{"time":316880,"text":"who had died a couple of months prior\ndue to alcohol-related liver disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322480,"text":"You see, assigning a letter\nto my father, a letter to my son,"},{"time":326360,"text":"\"If I knew then what I know now ...\""},{"time":328680,"text":"\"If I believed one\npositive thing about myself,"},{"time":331320,"text":"how would my life be different?\""},{"time":333160,"text":"gives the person an opportunity\nto be introspective,"},{"time":336880,"text":"go on the inside,"},{"time":338200,"text":"which is where all the answers are anyway."},{"time":340600,"text":"But it also gives them an opportunity"},{"time":342440,"text":"to share something with the court\nthat goes beyond their criminal record"},{"time":346440,"text":"and their charges."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349080,"text":"The next principle is neutrality."},{"time":351800,"text":"When increasing public trust\nin the justice system,"},{"time":355120,"text":"neutrality is paramount."},{"time":356920,"text":"The judge cannot be perceived\nto be favoring one side over the other."},{"time":361840,"text":"The judge has to make a conscious decision\nnot to say things like,"},{"time":365840,"text":"\"my officer,\" \"my prosecutor,\"\n\"my defense attorney.\""},{"time":369720,"text":"And this is challenging\nwhen we work in environments"},{"time":372520,"text":"where you have people\nassigned to your courts,"},{"time":375080,"text":"the same people coming\nin and out of your courts as well."},{"time":379120,"text":"When I think of neutrality,"},{"time":380600,"text":"I'm reminded of when I was\na new Rutgers Law grad"},{"time":384720,"text":"and freshly minted attorney,"},{"time":386800,"text":"and I entered an arbitration\nand I was greeted by two grey-haired men"},{"time":391320,"text":"who were joking about\nthe last game of golf they played together"},{"time":395160,"text":"and planning future social outings."},{"time":397480,"text":"I knew my client couldn't get\na fair shot in that forum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402000,"text":"The next principle is understand."},{"time":405440,"text":"It is critical that court participants\nunderstand the process,"},{"time":410720,"text":"the consequences of the process"},{"time":413120,"text":"and what's expected of them."},{"time":415200,"text":"I like to say that legalese\nis the language we use to confuse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":421600,"text":"I am keenly aware that the people\nwho appear before me,"},{"time":424360,"text":"many of them have very little education"},{"time":426960,"text":"and English is often\ntheir second language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429520,"text":"So I speak plain English in court."},{"time":432000,"text":"A great example of this\nwas when I was a young judge --"},{"time":434640,"text":"oh no, I mean younger judge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":437600,"text":"When I was a younger judge,\na senior judge comes to me,"},{"time":440240,"text":"gives me a script and says,"},{"time":441600,"text":"\"If you think somebody\nhas mental health issues,"},{"time":443880,"text":"ask them these questions\nand you can get your evaluation.\""},{"time":446640,"text":"So the first time I saw someone"},{"time":448200,"text":"who had what I thought\nwas a mental health issue,"},{"time":450560,"text":"I went for my script\nand I started to ask questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453040,"text":"\"Um, sir, do you take psycho --\num, psychotrop --"},{"time":456160,"text":"psychotropic medication?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":458480,"text":"\"Nope.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":460400,"text":"\"Uh, sir, have you treated\nwith a psychiatrist before?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":464560,"text":"\"Nope.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":465800,"text":"But it was obvious that the person\nwas suffering from mental illness."},{"time":469840,"text":"One day, in my frustration, I decided\nto scrap the script and ask one question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473600,"text":"\"Ma'am, do you take medication\nto clear your mind?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":476040,"text":"\"Yeah, judge, I take Haldol\nfor my schizophrenia,"},{"time":478680,"text":"Xanax for my anxiety.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":481240,"text":"The question works even when it doesn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483920,"text":"\"Mr. L, do you take medication\nto clear your mind?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":486680,"text":"\"No, judge, I don't take\nno medication to clear my mind."},{"time":489360,"text":"I take medication\nto stop the voices in my head,"},{"time":491800,"text":"but my mind is fine.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":493080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":494680,"text":"You see, once people\nunderstand the question,"},{"time":497760,"text":"they can give you valuable information"},{"time":499640,"text":"that allows the court\nto make meaningful decisions"},{"time":502040,"text":"about the cases that are before them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504920,"text":"The last principle is respect,"},{"time":507560,"text":"that without it none\nof the other principles can work."},{"time":511440,"text":"Now, respect can be as simple as,"},{"time":514200,"text":"\"Good afternoon, sir.\"\n\"Good morning, ma'am.\""},{"time":517000,"text":"It's looking the person in the eye\nwho is standing before you,"},{"time":520400,"text":"especially when you're sentencing them."},{"time":523159,"text":"It's when I say,\n\"Um, how are you doing today?"},{"time":525360,"text":"And what's going on with you?\""},{"time":526840,"text":"And not as a greeting,"},{"time":528120,"text":"but as someone who is\nactually interested in the response."},{"time":531840,"text":"Respect is the difference between saying,"},{"time":534760,"text":"\"Ma'am, are you having difficulty"},{"time":536400,"text":"understanding the information\nin the paperwork?\""},{"time":538800,"text":"versus, \"You can\nread and write, can't you?\""},{"time":541280,"text":"when you've realized\nthere's a literacy issue."},{"time":544520,"text":"And the good thing about respect\nis that it's contagious."},{"time":547240,"text":"People see you being\nrespectful to other folks"},{"time":549560,"text":"and they impute\nthat respect to themselves."},{"time":551960,"text":"You see, that's what\nthe transgender prostitute was telling me."},{"time":555680,"text":"I'm judging you just as much\nas you think you may be judging me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559480,"text":"Now, I am not telling you what I think,"},{"time":561920,"text":"I am telling you what I have lived,"},{"time":564000,"text":"using procedural justice\nto change the culture at my courthouse"},{"time":568560,"text":"and in the courtroom."},{"time":570640,"text":"After sitting comfortably for seven months"},{"time":573720,"text":"as a traffic court judge,"},{"time":575680,"text":"I was advised that I was being moved\nto the criminal court,"},{"time":579840,"text":"Part Two, criminal courtroom."},{"time":583040,"text":"Now, I need you to understand,"},{"time":584680,"text":"this was not good news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586920,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":587960,"text":"It was not."},{"time":589240,"text":"Part Two was known\nas the worst courtroom in the city,"},{"time":592640,"text":"some folks would even say in the state."},{"time":595200,"text":"It was your typical urban courtroom\nwith revolving door justice,"},{"time":599880,"text":"you know, your regular lineup\nof low-level offenders --"},{"time":602520,"text":"you know, the low-hanging fruit,"},{"time":604760,"text":"the drug-addicted prostitute,"},{"time":607200,"text":"the mentally ill homeless person\nwith quality-of-life tickets,"},{"time":611360,"text":"the high school dropout petty drug dealer\nand the misguided young people --"},{"time":616640,"text":"you know, those folks\ndoing a life sentence"},{"time":619120,"text":"30 days at a time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622120,"text":"Fortunately, the City of Newark\ndecided that Newarkers deserved better,"},{"time":625920,"text":"and they partnered\nwith the Center for Court Innovation"},{"time":628680,"text":"and the New Jersey Judiciary"},{"time":630120,"text":"to create Newark Community Solutions,"},{"time":632720,"text":"a community court program"},{"time":634840,"text":"that provided alternative sanctions."},{"time":637880,"text":"This means now a judge"},{"time":640360,"text":"can sentence a defendant\nto punishment with assistance."},{"time":644200,"text":"So a defendant who would\notherwise get a jail sentence"},{"time":646800,"text":"would now be able to get\nindividual counseling sessions,"},{"time":649480,"text":"group counseling sessions\nas well as community giveback,"},{"time":652200,"text":"which is what we call community service."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654920,"text":"The only problem is\nthat this wonderful program"},{"time":657560,"text":"was now coming to Newark\nand was going to be housed where?"},{"time":660520,"text":"Part Two criminal courtroom."},{"time":663000,"text":"And the attitudes there were terrible."},{"time":665800,"text":"And the reason that\nthe attitudes were terrible there"},{"time":668320,"text":"was because everyone who was sent there"},{"time":670240,"text":"understood they were\nbeing sent there as punishment."},{"time":672720,"text":"The officers who were facing\ndisciplinary actions at times,"},{"time":676360,"text":"the public defender and prosecutor"},{"time":678840,"text":"felt like they were doing\na 30-day jail sentence on their rotation,"},{"time":683040,"text":"the judges understood\nthey were being hazed"},{"time":685960,"text":"just like a college\nsorority or fraternity."},{"time":690160,"text":"I was once told that\nan attorney who worked there"},{"time":692520,"text":"referred to the defendants\nas \"the scum of the earth\""},{"time":696960,"text":"and then had to represent them."},{"time":699240,"text":"I would hear things from folks like,"},{"time":701000,"text":"\"Oh, how could you work\nwith those people? They're so nasty."},{"time":703880,"text":"You're a judge, not a social worker.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":706200,"text":"But the reality is that as a society,\nwe criminalize social ills,"},{"time":710680,"text":"then sent people to a judge\nand say, \"Do something.\""},{"time":714000,"text":"I decided that I was going\nto lead by example."},{"time":716840,"text":"So my first foray into the approach\ncame when a 60-something-year-old man"},{"time":720880,"text":"appeared before me handcuffed."},{"time":722960,"text":"His head was lowered and his body\nwas showing the signs of drug withdrawal."},{"time":727760,"text":"I asked him how long he had been addicted,\nand he said, \"30 years.\""},{"time":731600,"text":"And I asked him, \"Do you have any kids?\""},{"time":734600,"text":"And he said, \"Yeah,\nI have a 32-year-old son.\""},{"time":737120,"text":"And I said, \"Oh, so you've never\nhad the opportunity"},{"time":740240,"text":"to be a father to your son\nbecause of your addiction.\""},{"time":744560,"text":"He began to cry."},{"time":746800,"text":"I said, \"You know what,\nI'm going to let you go home,"},{"time":749320,"text":"and you'll come back in two weeks,"},{"time":751000,"text":"and when you come back, we'll give you\nsome assistance for your addiction.\""},{"time":754560,"text":"Surprisingly, two weeks passed\nand he was sitting the courtroom."},{"time":758480,"text":"When he came up, he said,\n\"Judge, I came back to court"},{"time":761080,"text":"because you showed me more love\nthan I had for myself.\""},{"time":764560,"text":"And I thought, my God,\nhe heard love from the bench?"},{"time":768240,"text":"I could do this all day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":770720,"text":"Because the reality is that\nwhen the court behaves differently,"},{"time":773880,"text":"then naturally people respond differently."},{"time":776600,"text":"The court becomes a place\nyou can go to for assistance,"},{"time":779680,"text":"like the 60-something-year-old\nschizophrenic homeless woman"},{"time":783440,"text":"who was in distress"},{"time":784880,"text":"and fighting with the voices in her head,"},{"time":786880,"text":"and barges into court,\nand screams, \"Judge!"},{"time":789280,"text":"I just came by to see how you were doing.\""},{"time":792280,"text":"I had been monitoring her case\nfor a couple of months,"},{"time":795000,"text":"her compliance with her medication,"},{"time":797040,"text":"and had just closed out her case\na couple of weeks ago."},{"time":800040,"text":"On this day she needed help,"},{"time":802680,"text":"and she came to court."},{"time":803960,"text":"And after four hours\nof coaxing by the judge,"},{"time":807400,"text":"the police officers and the staff,"},{"time":809720,"text":"she is convinced to get into the ambulance"},{"time":812560,"text":"that will take her to crisis unit"},{"time":814680,"text":"so that she can get her medication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817400,"text":"People become connected to their community"},{"time":820040,"text":"when the court changes,"},{"time":822200,"text":"like the 50-something-year-old man"},{"time":824640,"text":"who told me, \"Community service\nwas terrible, Judge."},{"time":827160,"text":"I had to clean the park,\nand it was full of empty heroin envelopes,"},{"time":830360,"text":"and the kids had to play there.\""},{"time":832600,"text":"As he wrung his hands, he confessed,"},{"time":835720,"text":"\"Judge, I realized that it was my fault,"},{"time":838160,"text":"because I used that same park to get high,"},{"time":841320,"text":"and before you sent me there\nto do community service,"},{"time":843840,"text":"I had never gone to the park\nwhen I wasn't high,"},{"time":846240,"text":"so I never noticed\nthe children playing there.\""},{"time":850120,"text":"Every addict in the courtroom\nlowered their head."},{"time":853120,"text":"Who better to teach that lesson?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":856600,"text":"It helps the court reset\nits relationship with the community,"},{"time":861840,"text":"like with the 20-something-year-old guy"},{"time":864120,"text":"who gets a job interview\nthrough the court program."},{"time":867800,"text":"He gets a job interview\nat an office cleaning company,"},{"time":870400,"text":"and he comes back to court to proudly say,"},{"time":872640,"text":"\"Judge, I even worked in my suit\nafter the interview,"},{"time":877360,"text":"because I wanted the guy to see\nhow bad I wanted the job.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":882400,"text":"It's what happens\nwhen a person in authority"},{"time":886080,"text":"treats you with dignity and respect,"},{"time":888480,"text":"like the 40-something-year-old guy\nwho struts down the aisle"},{"time":891800,"text":"and says, \"Judge,\ndo you notice anything different?\""},{"time":894600,"text":"And when I look up,"},{"time":895960,"text":"he's pointing at his new teeth"},{"time":898400,"text":"that he was able to get after getting\na referral from the program,"},{"time":901760,"text":"but he was able to get them\nto replace the old teeth"},{"time":905160,"text":"that he lost as a result\nof years of heroin addiction."},{"time":909000,"text":"When he looks in the mirror,"},{"time":910600,"text":"now he sees somebody who is worth saving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":913680,"text":"You see, I have a dream"},{"time":915680,"text":"and that dream is\nthat judges will use these tools"},{"time":919800,"text":"to revolutionize\nthe communities that they serve."},{"time":923040,"text":"Now, these tools\nare not miracle cure-alls,"},{"time":925800,"text":"but they get us light-years closer\nto where we want to be,"},{"time":929120,"text":"and where we want to be is a place\nthat people enter our halls of justice"},{"time":933560,"text":"and believe they will be treated\nwith dignity and respect"},{"time":936400,"text":"and know that justice\nwill be served there."},{"time":940040,"text":"Imagine that, a simple idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943200,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944440,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}